Emergency services are searching for a mother and baby who were swept away while crossing a river on the KZN North Coast on Monday. According to Paul Herbst of Medi Response it is believed that the mother, with her baby on her back, was crossing the Mvoti River, when they were both swept away. “Witnesses to the incident managed to get to safety and to call for help,” he said. By Monday midday the Medi Response search and rescue unit, together with SAPS K9 Search and Rescue, KwaDukuza Municipality lifeguards, SAPS Search and Rescue and SAPS divers, were still conducting a search and rescue operation for the mother and child, he said. “Rescue teams have deployed the Medi Response drone as well as search and rescue K9’s across the area. At this stage there have been no positive results and the search is ongoing,” said Herbst. *This is a developing story.